## Development in Sandbox

```sh
# sandbox
terraform -chdir=infra init --backend-config=env/sandbox/backend.hcl
terraform -chdir=infra fmt -recursive && terraform -chdir=infra validate
terraform -chdir=infra plan -var-file=envs/sandbox/terraform.tfvars

terraform -chdir=infra apply -auto-approve -var-file="env/sandbox/terraform.tfvars"

terraform -chdir=infra destroy -auto-approve -var-file="env/sandbox/terraform.tfvars"

# dev
terraform -chdir=infra init --backend-config=env/dev/backend.hcl -reconfigure
terraform -chdir=infra destroy -auto-approve -var-file="env/dev/terraform.tfvars"

# test
terraform -chdir=infra init --backend-config=env/test/backend.hcl -reconfigure
terraform -chdir=infra destroy -auto-approve -var-file="env/test/terraform.tfvars"
```

---

## Trivy Scan

```sh
# Basic local config scan
trivy config ./infra

# Scan tfvars
trivy config --tf-vars ./infra/env/dev/terraform.tfvars ./infra

# Include secret scanning
trivy fs --scanners secret,misconfig ./

# Focus on important issues only
trivy config --tf-vars env/dev/terraform.tfvars --severity HIGH,CRITICAL .
# output report
trivy config -f json -o trivy-config-report.json .

# scan a Terraform plan
terraform plan -out=tfplan
terraform show -json tfplan > tfplan.json
trivy config tfplan.json
```
